**Sec. 25C. Potential Liability on Foreign Accounts**

(a) **Exceptions to Repayment**  
A bank doesn't have to repay a deposit made at a foreign branch if:  
1. There is war, insurrection, or civil strife.  
2. A foreign government or entity takes action that stops repayment.  
Unless the bank has agreed in writing to repay under these conditions.

(b) **Regulations**  
The Board and Comptroller of the Currency can make rules to carry out this section
